task.desc: Monitoring of WebSphere MQ objects such as queues, topics...

measure.description: Is 1 if the status is running, otherwise 0. If the queue manager is currently starting or shutting down this is also 0
Retrieve the current status of the queue manager
Is 1 if the status is ended, otherwise 0. If the queue manager is currently starting or shutting down this is also 0
Elapsed time in seconds since the last message was submitted since the queue manager started. A value is only displayed for this parameter if MONQ is set to a value other than OFF for this queue.

Elapsed time in seconds since the last message retrieval happened since the queue manager started. A message being browsed does not count as a message being retrieved. A value is only displayed for this parameter if MONQ is set to a value other than OFF for this queue.

The number of handles that are currently open for input for the queue (either input-shared or input-exclusive). This does not include handles that are open for browse. For shared queues, the number returned applies only to the queue manager generating the reply. The number is not the total for all the queue managers in the queue-sharing group.

Age, in seconds, of the oldest message on the queue. The maximum displayable value is 999 999 999; if the age exceeds this value, 999 999 999 is displayed. A value is only displayed for this parameter if MONQ is set to a value other than OFF for this queue.

This is the number of handles that are currently open for output for the queue. For shared queues, the number returned applies only to the queue manager generating the reply. The number is not the total for all the queue managers in the queue-sharing group.
The current depth of the queue, that is, the number of messages on the queue. This includes both committed messages and uncommitted messages.
The number of applications currently publishing to the topic.
This is the number of subscribers for this topic string, including durable subscribers who are not currently connected.
Elapsed time in seconds since the last message was retrieved.
Elapsed time in seconds since the last restoration of the connection.
The number of messages that went through.
Elapsed time in seconds since the last message was retrieved.
Elapsed time in seconds since the last restoration of the connection.
The number of messages that went through.
